 POLICE in Anambra State have arrested one Sir Izuchukwu Nwabueze, a high chief,for allegedly defrauding an Anglican bishop and 10 others of N15 million. Nwabueze perpetrated the offence by posing as Assistant Inspector-General of Police AIG,  Danmallam Mohammed, police said. One of the suspect’s alleged victims a hotelier. Nwabueze was paraded on Wednesday. Zonal police spokesperson  Nkeiruka Nwode said the matter was being investigated. She said AIG Danmallam Mohammed, has told victims of the alleged fraud to report to the zonal police headquarters. 